          Our Editor Take

          Our Editor Take

          State Farm is a mixed bag when it comes to rates. It has good rates for certain types of drivers and very high rates for others. And unfortunately it lacks a lot of coverage types that are easy to find from its top competitors, which pushed down its rating in our analysis.

          On the upside of rates, State Farm generally has good rates for drivers who have caused an accident with injury or property damage. It also has lower-than-average rates for drivers with poor credit or a speeding ticket. There are a good number of discounts available, including a bundling discount averaging a generous 23% when you buy State Farm auto and homeowners insurance.

          If you have poor credit youâ€™ll likely want to look elsewhere for auto insurance: We found that State Farmâ€™s rates for drivers with poor credit were the highest among all the companies we evaluated, coming in at over $4,000 a year higher than the national average.

          If youâ€™re interested in usage-based insurance that tracks your driving, you can get a 10% enrollment discount for State Farmâ€™s Drive Safe & Save program. You can earn up to 30% discount at renewal time if your driving scores well, and your rates wonâ€™t go up if your driving isnâ€™t great.

          On the downside, State Farm does not offer accident forgiveness, new car replacement, a pay-per-mile insurance program or a vanishing deductible.

          Also, in our survey of State Farm customers, only 76% of customers who have made claims report that they are somewhat to completely satisfied with the claims process, compared to our survey average of 83%. The main pain points were a lack of communication about claims and lack of a timely resolution to claims.

          However, we found that 89% of State Farm customers had some level of satisfaction with customer service and pricing, which was slightly above average (86%).

          Pros

          • Will provide SR-22s.
          • Low level of complaints about State Farm auto insurance made to state insurance departments over the last three years.
          • Offers a good digital experience, including a mobile app with high user ratings, online quotes and the ability to buy a policy online

          Cons

          • Received only a C grade for the last four years from auto repair experts for its collision claim processes.
          • You can find better rates elsewhere for adding a teen driver.

          State Farm Overview

          State Farm was founded in 1922 by a retired farmer and insurance salesman George Jacob â€œG.J.â€ Mecherle. Although it began as an auto insurance company, State Farm now offers more than 100 different products and services across five different industries.

          State Farm is the largest auto insurance company in the U.S., with a market share of about 18% for private passenger auto insurance.

          State Farm AM Best Financial Strength Rating

          State Farm has an A++ (Superior) financial strength rating with AM Best, which is the top available rating.

          A high financial strength rating indicates a company will be able to pay future claims.

          State Farm Car Insurance Availability

          State Farm car insurance is available in all 48 states and Washington, D.C. for new policies. In Massachusetts and Rhode Island, State Farm is servicing only existing policyholders.

For example, State Farmâ€™s average price for a good driver is over 49% higher than Nationwideâ€™s average of $1,452 per year.

          Is State Farm good auto insurance?

          Yes, State Farm can provide good auto insurance. It has a low level of complaints and assigns you an agent for personalized service. But depending on your driver profile, it may be pricey.

          State Farmâ€™s costs for drivers with a DUI are fairly good, and itâ€™s competitive for drivers with a speeding ticket or who have caused an accident. But rates are very high for drivers with poor credit and those adding a teen driver.
